  28     version_pattern = r'\d+\.\d+(\.\d)?'
  29 
  30     def test_retrieves_version_of_self(self):
  31         pkg_version = version('egginfo-pkg')
  32         assert isinstance(pkg_version, text)
  33         assert re.match(self.version_pattern, pkg_version)
  34 
  35     def test_retrieves_version_of_distinfo_pkg(self):
  36         pkg_version = version('distinfo-pkg')
  37         assert isinstance(pkg_version, text)
  38         assert re.match(self.version_pattern, pkg_version)
  39 
  40     def test_for_name_does_not_exist(self):
  41         with self.assertRaises(PackageNotFoundError):
  42             distribution('does-not-exist')
  43 
  44     def test_for_top_level(self):
  45         self.assertEqual(
  46             distribution('egginfo-pkg').read_text('top_level.txt').strip(),
  47             'mod')
  48 
  49     def test_read_text(self):
  50         top_level = [
  51             path for path in files('egginfo-pkg')
  52             if path.name == 'top_level.txt'
  53             ][0]
  54         self.assertEqual(top_level.read_text(), 'mod\n')
  55 
  56     def test_entry_points(self):
  57         entries = dict(entry_points()['entries'])
  58         ep = entries['main']
  59         self.assertEqual(ep.value, 'mod:main')
  60         self.assertEqual(ep.extras, [])
  61 
  62     def test_metadata_for_this_package(self):
  63         md = metadata('egginfo-pkg')
  64         assert md['author'] == 'Steven Ma'
  65         assert md['LICENSE'] == 'Unknown'
  66         assert md['Name'] == 'egginfo-pkg'
  67         classifiers = md.get_all('Classifier')
  68         assert 'Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries' in classifiers
  69 
  70     def test_importlib_metadata_version(self):
  71         assert re.match(self.version_pattern, __version__)
  72 
  73     @staticmethod
  74     def _test_files(files):
  75         root = files[0].root
  76         for file in files:
  77             assert file.root == root
  78             assert not file.hash or file.hash.value
  79             assert not file.hash or file.hash.mode == 'sha256'
  80             assert not file.size or file.size >= 0
  81             assert file.locate().exists()
  82             assert isinstance(file.read_binary(), bytes)
  83             if file.name.endswith('.py'):
  84                 file.read_text()
  85 
  86     def test_file_hash_repr(self):
  87         try:
  88             assertRegex = self.assertRegex
  89         except AttributeError:
  90             # Python 2
  91             assertRegex = self.assertRegexpMatches
  92 
  93         util = [
  94             p for p in files('distinfo-pkg')
  95             if p.name == 'mod.py'
  96             ][0]
  97         assertRegex(
  98             repr(util.hash),
  99             '<FileHash mode: sha256 value: .*>')

 114     def test_requires_egg_info(self):
 115         deps = requires('egginfo-pkg')
 116         assert len(deps) == 2
 117         assert any(
 118             dep == 'wheel >= 1.0; python_version >= "2.7"'
 119             for dep in deps
 120             )
 121 
 122     def test_requires_dist_info(self):
 123         deps = requires('distinfo-pkg')
 124         assert len(deps) == 2
 125         assert all(deps)
 126         assert 'wheel >= 1.0' in deps
 127         assert "pytest; extra == 'test'" in deps
 128 
 129     def test_more_complex_deps_requires_text(self):
 130         requires = textwrap.dedent("""
 131             dep1
 132             dep2
 133 
 134             [:python_version < "3"]
 135             dep3
 136 
 137             [extra1]
 138             dep4
 139 
 140             [extra2:python_version < "3"]
 141             dep5
 142             """)
 143         deps = sorted(Distribution._deps_from_requires_text(requires))
 144         expected = [
 145             'dep1',
 146             'dep2',
 147             'dep3; python_version < "3"',
 148             'dep4; extra == "extra1"',
 149             'dep5; (python_version < "3") and extra == "extra2"',
 150             ]
 151         # It's important that the environment marker expression be
 152         # wrapped in parentheses to avoid the following 'and' binding more
 153         # tightly than some other part of the environment expression.
 154 
 155         assert deps == expected

 158 class OffSysPathTests(fixtures.DistInfoPkgOffPath, unittest.TestCase):
 159     def test_find_distributions_specified_path(self):
 160         dists = Distribution.discover(path=[str(self.site_dir)])
 161         assert any(
 162             dist.metadata['Name'] == 'distinfo-pkg'
 163             for dist in dists
 164             )
 165 
 166     def test_distribution_at_pathlib(self):
 167         """Demonstrate how to load metadata direct from a directory.
 168         """
 169         dist_info_path = self.site_dir / 'distinfo_pkg-1.0.0.dist-info'
 170         dist = Distribution.at(dist_info_path)
 171         assert dist.version == '1.0.0'
 172 
 173     def test_distribution_at_str(self):
 174         dist_info_path = self.site_dir / 'distinfo_pkg-1.0.0.dist-info'
 175         dist = Distribution.at(str(dist_info_path))
 176         assert dist.version == '1.0.0'
